.defvar *print-level*
.defvar1 prinlevel
3*print-level** can be set to the maximum number of nested lists that
can be printed before the printer gives up and just prints a 7#*
instead of a list element.  If it is 3nil*, which it is initially, any
number of nested lists can be printed.  Otherwise, the value of
3*print-level** must be a fixnum.  Example:
.lisp
